reviews.review_text: nice job recording this one. anyone else remember they had put speakers out on the street next to the civic center this night? As i recall they had them out there for 2 songs only?????   must have been the S F P D,making them stop. Anyway typical night in San Francisco. A friend of mine and myself were left out in the cold this night.  Bummer new years eve outside........   naaaaaaaah we missed the 1st set only. as we walked around the civic center we were told to go to the front door at 11:45. Much to my suprise we were there and wouldnt you know it in  the good old days they opened the front door and allowed us to enter.One of the ushers knew us from haight street. Thank you to this day.

great shakedown Used to have a video and tape but both were unfortunatly lost. Damn! But this show killed. Saw the first show of the run but couldn't get into this one. The Shakedown is one of if not the best I've heard. The rest of the show is killer also. Baby Blue is just soo sweet. I'm sure it was an ode to Parrish's wife and daughter. Listen and enjoy!
